DNS module provides asynchronous DNS resolution and domain name utilities.

**DNS Resolution**:
```javascript
const dns = require('dns');

// Resolve domain to IP
dns.resolve('google.com', (err, addresses) => {
  if (err) throw err;
  console.log('IP addresses:', addresses);
});

// Reverse DNS lookup
dns.reverse('8.8.8.8', (err, hostnames) => {
  if (err) throw err;
  console.log('Hostnames:', hostnames);
});
```

**Promise-based Methods**:
```javascript
const dns = require('dns').promises;

async function lookup() {
  try {
    const addresses = await dns.resolve4('google.com');
    console.log('IPv4 addresses:', addresses);

    const mx = await dns.resolveMx('google.com');
    console.log('MX records:', mx);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(err);
  }
}
```

**Record Types**:
- `resolve4()` - IPv4 addresses
- `resolve6()` - IPv6 addresses
- `resolveMx()` - Mail exchange records
- `resolveTxt()` - Text records
- `resolveSrv()` - Service records

DNS module enables network domain resolution in Node.js!

Child process module allows spawning subprocesses and running external commands from Node.js.

**Spawn (for long-running processes)**:
```javascript
