Querystring module provides utilities for parsing and formatting URL query strings in Node.js.

**Basic Parsing**:
```javascript
const querystring = require('querystring');

const qs = 'name=John&age=30&city=New+York';
const parsed = querystring.parse(qs);
console.log(parsed);
// { name: 'John', age: '30', city: 'New York' }
```

**Stringifying Objects**:
```javascript
const obj = { name: 'John', age: 30, city: 'New York' };
const str = querystring.stringify(obj);
console.log(str);
// 'name=John&age=30&city=New+York'
```

**Advanced Options**:
```javascript
// Custom delimiter and separator
const qs = 'name:John|age:30|city:New York';
const parsed = querystring.parse(qs, { delimiter: '|', separator: ':' });
console.log(parsed);
// { name: 'John', age: '30', city: 'New York' }
```

**URL Encoding**:
```javascript
const obj = { message: 'Hello World!' };
const encoded = querystring.stringify(obj, '&', '=', {
  encodeURIComponent: (str) => {
    return encodeURIComponent(str).replace(/%20/g, '+');
  }
});
```

**Escaping Characters**:
```javascript
const str = 'name=John&age=30&city=New York';
const escaped = querystring.escape(str);
const unescaped = querystring.unescape(escaped);
```

**Modern Alternative**:
```javascript
