Nullish coalescing (??) is a logical operator that returns its right-hand operand when its left-hand operand is null or undefined.

**Basic Nullish Coalescing**:
```javascript
// With nullish coalescing
const name = null ?? 'Anonymous';
console.log(name); // Anonymous

const age = undefined ?? 25;
console.log(age); // 25

// With actual values
const city = 'NYC' ?? 'Unknown';
console.log(city); // NYC

const count = 0 ?? 10;
console.log(count); // 0 (not falsy, so keeps 0)
```

**Comparison with OR Operator**:
```javascript
// OR operator (||) - treats all falsy values as empty
const value1 = 0 || 10;
console.log(value1); // 10

const value2 = '' || 'default';
console.log(value2); // default

const value3 = false || true;
console.log(value3); // true

// Nullish coalescing (??) - only null/undefined
const value4 = 0 ?? 10;
console.log(value4); // 0

const value5 = '' ?? 'default';
console.log(value5); // ''

const value6 = false ?? true;
console.log(value6); // false
```

**Practical Examples**:
```javascript
// Function parameters
function greet(name = null) {
  const displayName = name ?? 'Guest';
  console.log(`Hello, ${displayName}!`);
}

greet('John'); // Hello, John!
greet(null); // Hello, Guest!
greet(undefined); // Hello, Guest!

// Configuration objects
const config = {
  port: 3000,
  host: null,
  timeout: undefined,
  retries: 0
};

const port = config.port ?? 8080;
const host = config.host ?? 'localhost';
const timeout = config.timeout ?? 5000;
const retries = config.retries ?? 3;

console.log(port, host, timeout, retries); // 3000 localhost 5000 0
```

**Chaining Nullish Coalescing**:
```javascript
const user = {
  profile: {
    name: null,
    age: undefined
  }
};

// Chained nullish coalescing
const name = user?.profile?.name ?? user?.profile?.displayName ?? 'Unknown';
console.log(name); // Unknown

// Multiple fallbacks
const getValue = (obj) => obj?.value1 ?? obj?.value2 ?? obj?.value3 ?? 'default';
```

**With Optional Chaining**:
```javascript
const data = {
  user: null,
  settings: {
    theme: undefined
  }
};

// Perfect combination
const userName = data?.user?.name ?? 'Anonymous';
const theme = data?.settings?.theme ?? 'light';

console.log(userName, theme); // Anonymous light
```

**Use Cases**:
- Default values
- Configuration handling
- API response processing
- Form validation
- Error handling
- Safe property access

Nullish coalescing provides more precise control over default values!

